
                                            President Zuma unveiled a statue of the longest serving ANC president on Thursday.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma says that advancing radical economic transformation would be a fitting tribute to the late OR Tambo.  Zuma unveiled a statue of the longest serving ANC president on Thursday. WATCH: Zuma unveils OR Tambo statue  Tambo was born on 27 October 1917 in Mbizana and died in 1993. The African National Congress and its alliance partners have dedicated this year honouring him through various events. Zuma says it's important to use this year of OR Tambo to seek an inclusive economy. “We will then be paying a fitting tribute to OR Tambo, who wanted to see progress or development for the people of our country.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)